Seven people have died and two are in critical condition after a road accident in Kisian area within Kisumu county. Kisumu county police commander Ranson Lolmondoni said that the trailer which was ferrying Sugar cane lost control and rammed into two vehicles and a Nissan which was heading to Busia on Monday. According to a witness, Walter Odinde, the lorry might have lost control before it rammed into the Nissan hitting other vehicles. "All the people in the Nissan died instantly, but we managed to save a three month old baby, and the conductor of the Nissan," he said. The driver of the lorry carrying sugarcane tried to escape but was caught by members of the public who beat him up. He was saved by officers and also currently fighting for his life. The lorry was burnt by the area locals.